    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-11-25T02:16:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-11-25T02:16:00-05:00" n="94"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d94">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 124.71/4</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Roumania</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_VCJ1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Vopicka</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucharest</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-25T09:00:00+01:44">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 25, 1916, 9 a. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 30, 11.15 a. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>384. The diplomatic corps, as well as Roumanian Court and Government officials,
                    are leaving for Jassy this evening where the seat of Roumanian Government has
                    been removed. I am remaining in Bucharest and sending Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_AWW1">Andrews</persName> to Jassy as per Department’s telegram
                    dated September 23, 4 p. m.<note n="1" xml:id="d94fn1">Not printed.</note> The
                    Bulgarian and German armies have crossed the Danube, and it is expected that
                    they will enter Bucharest within a few days. Conditions are serious and city is
                    in a panic. People leaving by all kinds of conveyances.</p>
                <p>Have been requested by British, Russian, Italian, Serbian Ministers to take
                    charge of their interests, and have accepted subject to the approval of
                    Department. Please send third secretary as soon as possible. Please inform my
                    wife my health is fairly good.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vopicka</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
